      <img src="/static14/tech/2026/06/09/from-the-data-center-to-the-edge-how-to-build-secure-effective-enterprise-ai-infrastructure.webp" alt="From the data center to the edge: How to build secure, effective enterprise AI infrastructure" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">From the data center to the edge: How to build secure, effective enterprise AI infrastructure</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      While hyperscalers and neo-cloud providers may get the lion’s share of attention for providing AI infrastructure, many enterprises are taking a build-it-themselves approach to meet their specific AI requirements.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2026/06/09/from-the-data-center-to-the-edge-how-to-build-secure-effective-enterprise-ai-infrastructure/"  >(Network World)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
</div><div class="column text"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Wed, 10 Jun 2026 04:21:42 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Wed, 10 Jun 2026 04:21:42 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Computer World">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/tech/2026/06/10/uk-move-to-filter-photos-and-messages-triggers-encryption-worries-for-cisos-2.webp" alt="UK move to filter photos and messages triggers encryption worries for CISOs" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">UK move to filter photos and messages triggers encryption worries for CISOs</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer’s speech on Monday insisting that tech companies create device controls to somehow block children from viewing or creating sexually explicit imagery has raised alarms among CISOs, who worry that the same technology could undermine enterprise security.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2026/06/10/uk-move-to-filter-photos-and-messages-triggers-encryption-worries-for-cisos-2/"  >(Computer World)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Fri, 12 Jun 2026 16:00:00 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Fri, 12 Jun 2026 16:00:00 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Adam Bluestein, Fast Company">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/tech/2026/06/12/space-investing-moon-near-earth.webp" alt="Beyond the SpaceX IPO: Where the smart money in space is going" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Beyond the SpaceX IPO: Where the smart money in space is going</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      While SpaceX’s IPO captures global financial headlines, a high-stakes space ecosystem has been quietly emerging.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2026/06/12/space-investing-moon-near-earth/"  >(Adam Bluestein, Fast Company)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Thu, 11 Jun 2026 13:01:27 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Thu, 11 Jun 2026 13:01:27 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Glenn Gamboa, Associated Press, KPRC 2">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/tech/2026/06/11/anthropic-announces-claude-corps-to-teach-nonprofits-to-use-ai-more-effectively.webp" alt="Anthropic announces 'Claude Corps' to teach nonprofits to use AI more effectively" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Anthropic announces 'Claude Corps' to teach nonprofits to use AI more effectively</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      Anthropic will donate $150 million to launch a fellowship program called Claude Corps that plans to help nonprofits effectively use artificial intelligence by embedding 1,000 trained fellows in various organizations for a year.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2026/06/11/anthropic-announces-claude-corps-to-teach-nonprofits-to-use-ai-more-effectively/"  >(Glenn Gamboa, Associated Press, KPRC 2)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
</div><div class="column hcwi"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Thu, 11 Jun 2026 17:03:47 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Thu, 11 Jun 2026 17:03:47 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Computer World">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/tech/2026/06/11/wwdc-what-it-admins-need-to-know.webp" alt="WWDC: What IT admins need to know" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">WWDC: What IT admins need to know</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      Under-the-hood AI changes and efficiency improvements at the OS layer across Apple’s platforms are certainly the highlights at WWDC 2026. But there have also been significant changes IT admins will need to prepare for, particularly around Declarative Device Management (DDM).
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2026/06/11/wwdc-what-it-admins-need-to-know/"  >(Computer World)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Thu, 11 Jun 2026 15:30:00 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Thu, 11 Jun 2026 15:30:00 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Sam Byford, Fast Company">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/tech/2026/06/11/apple-new-watch-software-watchos27-older-models.webp" alt="Apple&#8217;s new watch software won&#8217;t run on some of its older models" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Apple&#8217;s new watch software won&#8217;t run on some of its older models</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      Apple just wrapped up its annual round of WWDC announcements, and, as usual, there wasn’t any new hardware.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2026/06/11/apple-new-watch-software-watchos27-older-models/"  >(Sam Byford, Fast Company)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Tue, 09 Jun 2026 14:15:30 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Tue, 09 Jun 2026 14:15:30 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Network World">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/tech/2026/06/09/ai-inference-moving-to-private-clouds-broadcom-says.webp" alt="AI inference moving to private clouds, Broadcom says" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">AI inference moving to private clouds, Broadcom says</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      The majority of enterprises now either run or plan to run AI workloads in private clouds, according to a survey of 1,800 senior IT decision makers conducted by Radius Tech on behalf of Broadcom. Only 41% of enterprises are now using public clouds for inference workloads, down from 56% last year.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2026/06/09/ai-inference-moving-to-private-clouds-broadcom-says/"  >(Network World)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
</div></div></fieldset><fieldset><legend><h2>
